2 SENATE BILL 581
1 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
2 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
3 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
4 Article – State Finance and Procurement
5 3.5–304.
6 (A) The Secretary shall develop a statewide information technology master plan.
7 (B) (1) THE PLAN DEVELOPED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION
8 SHALL BE POSTED PUBLICLY ON THE DEPARTMENT’S WEBSITE AND, IN
9 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, SUBMITTED TO
10 THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY WITHIN 6 MONTHS 1 YEAR AFTER THE DATE THE
11 GOVERNOR IS INAUGURATED IN THE GOVERNOR’S FIRST EACH GUBERNATORIAL
12 TERM.
13 (2) IF THE SECRETARY IS UNABLE TO MEET THE DEADLINE
14 ESTABLISHED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION, WITHIN 10 DAYS AFTER
15 THE MISSED DEADLINE, THE SECRETARY SHALL NOTIFY THE GOVERNOR IN
16 WRITING AND, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT
17 ARTICLE:
18 (I) THE SENATE BUDGET AND TAXATION COMMITTEE;
19 (II) THE SENATE COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION, ENERGY, AND
20 THE ENVIRONMENT;
21 (III) THE HOUSE APPROPRIATIONS COMMITTEE;
22 (IV) THE HOUSE GOVERNMENT, LABOR, AND ELECTIONS
23 COMMITTEE; AND
24 (V) THE JOINT COMMITTEE ON CYBERSECURITY,
25 INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, AND BIOTECHNOLOGY.
26 (3) THE NOTICE REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS
27 SUBSECTION SHALL INCLUDE AN EXPLANATION OF WHY THE PLAN IS DELAYED AND
28 PROVIDE A DATE FOR ITS PUBLICATION, NOT TO EXCEED 3 MONTHS AFTER THE
29 DEADLINE ESTABLISHED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
30 (C) EACH YEAR, THE SECRETARY, OR THE SECRETARY’S DESIGNEE, SHALL
31 PROVIDE A BRIEFING TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY ON:

SENATE BILL 581 3
1 (1) THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THE PLAN;
2 (2) ANY MATERIAL CHANGES MADE TO THE PLAN; AND
3 (3) HOW THE STATE INTENDS TO MANAGE AND DEPLOY THE
4 INITIATIVES INCLUDED IN THE PLAN ACROSS THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH OF STATE
5 GOVERNMENT.
6 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
7 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
